('3080', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly butter a medium or large baking dish.'),
('3080', '2', 'Rinse and dry fillets. Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.'),
('3080', '3', 'In a skillet or frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.'),
('3080', '4', 'Saute onion in butter until golden. Stir in flour until completely incorporated. Stir in mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, light and heavy creams. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.'),
('3080', '5', 'Remove from heat and stir in cheeses.'),
('3080', '6', 'Pour sauce over fish and sprinkle with paprika.'),
('3080', '7', 'Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, until brown and bubbly.'),
('3081', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375F.'),
('3081', '2', 'Cook onions in butter in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until softened and just beginning to brown, 7 to 8 minutes.'),
('3081', '3', 'Remove skillet from heat and stir in haddock, 1 tablespoon parsley, and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('3081', '4', 'Halve or quarter celery root to fit slicer. Thinly slice potatoes and celery root (about 1/8-inch thick) with slicer. Layer one third of potatoes and celery root in buttered baking dish.'),
('3081', '5', 'Spread half of haddock mixture on top, then repeat layering with half of remaining vegetables, all of remaining haddock mixture, and then remaining vegetables. Stir together cream, milk, salt, and pepper and pour on top of gratin, then cover dish tightly with buttered foil.'),
('3081', '6', 'Bake gratin in middle of oven until vegetables are just tender, about 1 hour. Uncover and bake, basting 2 or 3 times with pan juices, until top is golden, about 30 minutes more.'),
('3081', '7', 'Let stand 10 minutes, then sprinkle with remaining tablespoon parsley.'),
('3081', '8', '* Available at Asian cookware shops.'),
('3083', '1', 'Place the haddock in a deep baking tray with the milk and bay leaves, then cover the tray with foil and cook for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, cook the potatoes in salted boiling water for about 15 minutes, until soft.'),
('3083', '2', 'Drain them in a colander to get rid of any excess water, then return to the pan on a low heat and mash.Flake the cooked fish into a large bowl, picking out any bones and removing the skin.'),
('3083', '3', 'Add the mashed potato, parsley, mint, lemon and lime zest, fennels seeds, eggs and chilli and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),
('3083', '4', 'Mix well, taste and add more salt if necessary.Flour your work surface, then take 1 tablespoon of the mix in your hands with a little flour and pat it into a flattened circle, rolling it in the flour. Rough and ready is good, so dont worry about having them all exactly the same!'),
('3083', '5', 'Pour enough oil into a large heavy-bottomed saucepan to fill the pan about a third of the way up.'),
('3083', '6', 'Heat over a medium heat until a deep-frying thermometer inserted into the oil reaches 185C/360F. (If you dont have a thermometer, heat the oil until a cube of bread will brown in about 3 minutes.) Deep-fry the fishcakes for about 5 minutes until brown and crispy.'),
('3083', '7', 'Drain on kitchen paper, sprinkle with sea salt and serve on a large plate with lots of lemon halves.Tip'),
('3084', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly butter a 2-quart casserole or baking dish large enough to hold haddock fillets in a single layer.'),
('3084', '2', 'Melt 1 tablespoon of the butter in a skillet over medium heat and cook the onion slices, stirring occasionally, until soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in spinach and nutmeg  and cook for about 3 minutes.'),
('3084', '3', 'Arrange haddock fillets in baking dish. Spoon equal portions of the spinach mixture between the fillets. Spoon drained tomatoes around fillets and sprinkle with the thyme, tarragon and salt.'),
('3084', '4', 'Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3084', '5', 'While fish is baking, make the sauce. If necessary add enough water to reserved tomato liquid to make 1 cup.  In the skillet, melt the remaining 1 tablespoon butter over medium heat. Stir in the minced onion and cook until soft, about 5 minutes.'),
('3084', '6', 'Add 3/4 cup of the tomato juice to the onions. Bring mixture to a boil.'),
('3084', '7', 'Whisk the cornstarch into the remaining 1/4 cup juice, then add to the skillet. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring, until sauce thickens slightly.'),
('3084', '8', 'Pour sauce over baked fillets and serve.'),
('3094', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly butter a 2 quart casserole dish.'),
('3094', '2', 'Arrange fish fillets in the bottom of the prepared casserole dish, and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Layer onion slices over fish.'),
('3094', '3', 'Spread cream of mushroom soup over all, and top with shredded cheese.'),
('3094', '4', 'Bake in preheated oven for about 40 minutes, or until bubbly and fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3096', '1', 'Make the batter by mixing all the ingredients except for the fish and the oil in a large mixing bowl.'),
('3096', '2', 'Remove the skin and any bones from the fish fillets.'),
('3096', '3', 'Pour the oil into a wide and deep pan (we used a wok), turn on the heat to medium and heat the oil to 140c (if you dont have a thermometer, drop a few drops of the batter into the oil when its hot, the batter should immediately start bubbling and rise to the surface).'),
('3096', '4', 'Put the fish fillets into the bowl of batter and mix them around so that they are all completely covered. Then, one at a time, pick them out and carefully put them into the oil, making sure you dont overcrowd the pan (there should be plenty of space around each one, so do it in batches if necessary).Cook the fish for about 8 minutes, until they are a medium golden brown. While they are cooking, turn them over regularly and drop some of the batter from the bowl onto each piece (this gives it an interesting texture).When the fish is cooked, carefully take it out of the oil and put it onto some kitchen paper to drain off the excess fat (if you are cooking the fish in batches, put the cooked fish into a 100c oven to keep warm).'),
('3096', '5', 'Serve. We served it with chips, tinned mushy peas and tartar sauce.'),
('3098', '1', 'Cook and stir bacon in large saucepan until crisp.  Use slotted spoon to remove bacon from pan. drain on paper towels.  Discard all but 1 Tbsp. drippings from pan.'),
('3098', '2', 'Add next 3 ingredients to reserved drippings in pan. cook on medium heat 12 to 14 min. or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.'),
('3098', '3', 'Add broth and potatoes. stir.  Bring to boil. cover.  Simmer 10 to 12 min. or until potatoes are tender.'),
('3098', '4', 'Add cream cheese spread. cook, uncovered, 2 to 3 min. or until melted, stirring frequently.'),
('3098', '5', 'Add milk, fish and bacon. stir.  Bring to boil, stirring frequently.  Cook 3 to 4 min. or until fish flakes easily with fork.'),
('3099', '1', 'Whisk mayonnaise, yogurt, vinegar and crushed red pepper to taste in a medium bowl.'),
('3099', '2', 'Add pineapple and coleslaw mix and stir to combine.'),
('3099', '3', 'Place cornmeal in a shallow dish. Sprinkle both sides of fish with Cajun seasoning and salt. Dredge the fish in the cornmeal.'),
('3099', '4', 'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3099', '5', 'Add half the fish and cook until golden, about 2 minutes per side.'),
('3099', '6', 'Transfer to a plate and repeat with the remaining 2 teaspoons oil and fish, adjusting heat as needed to prevent burning.Top toasted bread with the fish and pineapple slaw to make sandwiches.'),
('3099', '7', 'Serve immediately.'),
('3103', '1', 'Melt 50g butter in a large saucepan (about 20cm across), add 1 finely chopped medium onion and cook gently over a medium heat for 5 minutes, until softened but not browned.'),
('3103', '2', 'Stir in 3 split cardamom pods,  tsp turmeric, 1 small cinnamon stick and 2 bay leaves, then cook for 1 minute.'),
('3103', '3', 'Tip in 450g basmati rice and stir until it is all well coated in the spicy butter.'),
('3103', '4', 'Pour in 1 litre chicken or fish stock, add  teaspoon salt and bring to the boil, stir once to release any rice from the bottom of the pan. Cover with a close-fitting lid, reduce the heat to low and leave to cook very gently for 12 minutes.'),
('3103', '5', 'Meanwhile, bring some water to the boil in a large shallow pan.'),
('3103', '6', 'Add 750g un-dyed smoked haddock fillet and simmer for 4 minutes, until the fish is just cooked. Lift it out onto a plate and leave until cool enough to handle.'),
('3103', '7', 'Hard-boil 3 eggs for 8 minutes.'),
('3103', '8', 'Flake the fish, discarding any skin and bones.'),
('3103', '9', 'Drain the eggs, cool slightly, then peel and chop.'),
('3103', '10', 'Uncover the rice and remove the bay leaves, cinnamon stick and cardamom pods if you wish to. Gently fork in the fish and the chopped eggs, cover again and return to the heat for 2-3 minutes, or until the fish has heated through.'),
('3103', '11', 'Gently stir in almost all the 3 tbsp chopped fresh parsley, and season with a little salt and black pepper to taste.'),
('3103', '12', 'Serve scattered with the remaining parsley and garnished with 1 lemon, cut into wedges.'),
('3104', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 375F (190C).'),
('3104', '2', 'Place the smoked haddock in a baking dish with 3 tbsp water. Cover with aluminum foil.'),
('3104', '3', 'Bake for 15 minutes, until heated through. Uncover and let cool, then flake into pieces.'),
('3104', '4', 'Mix the flaked haddock, mashed potato, scallions, parsley, lemon zest and juice, and mustard together in a bowl. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('3104', '5', 'Divide the mixture into 12 cakes.'),
('3104', '6', 'Place the flour in a small dish, the beaten egg in another, and the bread crumbs in a third dish.'),
('3104', '7', 'Roll each fishcake in the flour, then dip into the egg, and coat with the bread crumbs.'),
('3104', '8', 'Heat the oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. In batches, add the cakes and cook about 5 minutes, turning once, until golden brown.'),
('3104', '9', 'Transfer to paper towels to drain.'),
('3104', '10', 'Serve hot.'),
